      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCAR (3) has been racing in great heart and kept the ball rolling last start when he drew wider and worked but fought on well at Geelong, beaten 3 metres. That was his third runner-up result from his last four outings so the hoof is on the till. Draws well and should get his chance. PARIS JAMILLA (8) overcame a wide barrier when successful last time out by 4 metres in a nice return to form at Kilmore. Races very well third-up with two wins and a placing from four attempts so should be peaking. If she gets the gaps she could strike again. ROMANTIC NINA (7) draws wide but must be considered after coming from the second line to place in her last two starts. KYVALLEY ANTHONY (4) came from wider to score two back at Bendigo and was good again when third at Kilmore a week ago. Respect.",
